  "uuid": "d8bc66cd72e68d67d210cd1c0b6295b1",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Promoter (Acerpure)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:<br>\n</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1. Event Execution</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Participate in roadshows or events per month (lasting 4-7 days each), providing on-site support, product demonstrations, and promotions.</li>\n  <li>Manage the setup of roadshow/event sites, ensuring booths align with the company’s branding and display standards.</li>\n  <li>When no events are scheduled, work as a promoter at designated stores to enhance product exposure and drive sales.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Store Visits &amp; Materials Management</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct store visits (possibly 40+) per month to update display models, distribute POP materials and flyers, and check inventory.</li>\n  <li>Record visit data, compile reports, and upload photos to Google Drive for documentation.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3. Product Training</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Gain in-depth knowledge of company products and deliver training sessions to promoters, ensuring they possess strong product expertise and sales skills.<br>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimum 'O’ Level qualification.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of household appliances is an advantage.</li>\n  <li>Prior experience in retail is preferred.</li>\n  <li>Good interpersonal and communication skills.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Other Information:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Basic + Commission + Incentive Up To $3k/month or more</li>\n  <li>6 Off Days a month (flexible scheduling required)</li>\n  <li>Willing to work retail hours 1pm - 9pm, including weekend and PH (adapting to event and promotional schedules)</li>\n  <li>Attractive Staff Benefits (Flexible benefits, insurance coverage, annual leave)</li>\n  <li>Exciting learning opportunities to grow your skills and advance your career</li>\n  <li>Employed directly under Acer Computer (Singapore) Pte Ltd</li>\n</ul>",
